                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890d.00/192: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-08-10T12:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1925—noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of August 7, 2 p.m. You are instructed to use your discretion, in
                    consultation with the consul at Damascus, as to what action to take with respect
                    to advising American citizens in the region affected by the Druse revolt to go
                    to Beirut.</p>
                <p>There are two United States destroyers in the Adriatic. If you think it
                    necessary, the Department will take up with the Navy Department the question of
                    sending one or both of them to Beirut or to Alexandria, from where they could
                    easily go to Beirut if needed.</p>
                <p>Telegraph report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
